<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-15] redirect not handled correctly if location header doesn&apos;t have a protocol</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-15</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>Http redirect is not handled correctly if the location header doesn&amp;#39;t have a &lt;br/&gt;
protocol, e.g.:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Location: web/tbghome.nsf/pages/index&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
a java.net.MalformedURLException is throw in this case. The correct behavior is &lt;br/&gt;
to inherit the protocol from current URL.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The relevant code is in HttpMethodBase.execute()</description>
                <environment>Operating System: All&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other</environment>
